+## Discord commands
+
+The bot listens for commands on its Discord channel.  Commands follow the form
+`<Prefix> -<action> [args]` (case-insensitive).
+
+| Prefix | Typical use |
+|---|---|
+| `TradeBot` / `TB` | Trading control: start, stop, reset, portfolio, planned |
+| `WatchDog` / `WD` | Monitoring: status, pause, clearchat |
+| `Auditor` / `Au` | Audit, proposals, Q&A chat |
+| *(none)* | `help`, `whoami` |
+
+**Quick reference:**
+
+```
+TradeBot -portfolio      Current holdings + PnL
+TradeBot -planned        What the bot is weighing
+TradeBot -reset          Fresh paper start
+WatchDog -status         Health check
+Auditor  -review         Full audit
+Auditor  -pending        Proposals waiting for approval
+Auditor  -confirm <id>   Apply a proposal (then restart)
+Auditor  -ask <question> Single-shot question
+help                     All commands at a glance
+```
+
+Full command reference: [`DISCORD_COMMANDS.txt`](DISCORD_COMMANDS.txt)
